move_356.description:
Gravity is intensified
for five turns, making
moves involving flying
unusable and
negating Levitation.

move_357.name: miracle-eye
move_357.description:
Enables the user to
hit a Ghost type with
any type of move. It
also enables the user
to hit an evasive foe.

move_358.name: wake-up-slap
move_358.description:
This attack inflicts
high damage on a
sleeping foe. It
also wakes the foe
up, however.

move_359.name: hammer-arm
move_359.description:
The user swings and
hits with its strong
and heavy fist.
It lowers the user’s
Speed, however.

move_360.name: gyro-ball
move_360.description:
The user tackles the
foe with a high-speed
spin. The slower the
user, the greater
the damage.

move_361.name: healing-wish
move_361.description:
The user faints. In
return, the Pokémon
taking its place will
have its HP restored
and status cured.

move_362.name: brine
move_362.description:
If the foe’s HP is
down to about half,
this attack will hit
with double the
power.

move_363.name: natural-gift
move_363.description:
The user draws power
to attack by using
its held Berry.
The Berry determines
its type and power.

move_364.name: feint
move_364.description:
An attack that hits a
foe using Protect or
Detect. It also lifts
the effects of those
moves.

move_365.name: pluck
move_365.description:
The user pecks the
foe. If the foe is
holding a Berry, the
user plucks it and
gains its effect.

move_366.name: tailwind
move_366.description:
The user whips up a
turbulent whirlwind
that ups the Speed
of all party Pokémon
for three turns.

move_367.name: acupressure
move_367.description:
The user applies
pressure to stress
points, sharply
boosting one of its
stats.

move_368.name: metal-burst
move_368.description:
The user retaliates
against the foe that
last inflicted damage
on it with much
greater power.

move_369.name: u-turn
move_369.description:
After making its
attack, the user
rushes back to switch
places with a party
Pokémon in waiting.

move_370.name: close-combat
move_370.description:
The user fights the
foe in close without
guarding itself. It
also cuts the user’s
Defense and Sp. Def.

move_371.name: payback
move_371.description:
If the user can use
this attack after the
foe attacks, its
power is doubled.

move_372.name: assurance
move_372.description:
If the foe has
already taken some
damage in the same
turn, this attack’s
power is doubled.

move_373.name: embargo
move_373.description:
It prevents the foe
from using its held
item. Its Trainer is
also prevented from
using items on it.

move_374.name: fling
move_374.description:
The user flings its
held item at the foe
to attack. Its power
and effects depend
on the item.

move_375.name: psycho-shift
move_375.description:
Using its psychic
power of suggestion,
the user transfers
its status problems
to the target.

move_376.name: trump-card
move_376.description:
The fewer PP this move has, the greater
its attack power.

move_377.name: heal-block
move_377.description:
The user prevents
the foe from using
any HP-recovery
moves for five turns.

move_378.name: wring-out
move_378.description:
The user powerfully
wrings the foe.
The more HP the foe
has, the greater this
attack’s power.

move_379.name: power-trick
move_379.description:
The user employs its
psychic power to
switch its Attack
with its Defense
stat.

move_380.name: gastro-acid
move_380.description:
The user hurls up its
stomach acids on
the foe. The fluid
eliminates the effect
of the foe’s ability.

move_381.name: lucky-chant
move_381.description:
The user chants an
incantation toward
the sky, preventing
the foe from landing
critical hits.

move_382.name: me-first
move_382.description:
The user tries to cut
ahead of the foe to
steal and use the
foe’s intended move
with greater power.

move_383.name: copycat
move_383.description:
The user mimics the
move used immediately
before it. The move
fails if no other move
has been used yet.

move_384.name: power-swap
move_384.description:
The user employs its
psychic power to
switch changes to
its Attack and
Sp. Atk with the foe.

move_385.name: guard-swap
move_385.description:
The user employs its
psychic power to
switch changes to
its Defense and
Sp. Def with the foe.

move_386.name: punishment
move_386.description:
This attack’s power
increases the more
the foe has powered
up with stat changes.

move_387.name: last-resort
move_387.description:
This move can be used
only after the user
has used all the
other moves it knows
in the battle.

move_388.name: worry-seed
move_388.description:
A seed that causes
worry is planted on
the foe. It prevents
sleep by making its
ability Insomnia.

move_389.name: sucker-punch
move_389.description:
This move enables the
user to attack first.
It fails if the foe is
not readying an
attack, however.

move_390.name: toxic-spikes
move_390.description:
The user lays a trap
of poison spikes at
the foe’s feet. They
poison foes that
switch into battle.

move_391.name: heart-swap
move_391.description:
The user employs its psychic power to switch stat
changes with the target.

move_392.name: aqua-ring
move_392.description:
The user envelops
itself in a veil made
of water. It regains
some HP on every
turn.

move_393.name: magnet-rise
move_393.description:
The user levitates
using electrically
generated magnetism
for five turns.

move_394.name: flare-blitz
move_394.description:
The user cloaks
itself in fire and
charges at the foe.
The user sustains
serious damage, too.

move_395.name: force-palm
move_395.description:
The foe is attacked
with a shock wave.
It may also leave the
target paralyzed.

move_396.name: aura-sphere
move_396.description:
The user looses a
blast of aura power
from deep within its
body. This move is
certain to hit.

move_397.name: rock-polish
move_397.description:
The user polishes its
body to reduce drag.
It can sharply raise
the Speed stat.

move_398.name: poison-jab
move_398.description:
The foe is stabbed
with a tentacle or
arm steeped in
poison. It may also
poison the foe.

move_399.name: dark-pulse
move_399.description:
The user releases a
horrible aura imbued
with dark thoughts.
It may also make the
target flinch.

move_400.name: night-slash
move_400.description:
The user slashes the
foe the instant an
opportunity arises.
It has a high
critical-hit ratio.

move_401.name: aqua-tail
move_401.description:
The user attacks by
swinging its tail as if
it were a vicious wave
in a raging storm.

move_402.name: seed-bomb
move_402.description:
The user slams a
barrage of hard-
shelled seeds
down on the foe
from above.

move_403.name: air-slash
move_403.description:
The user attacks with
a blade of air that
slices even the sky.
It may also make the
target flinch.

move_404.name: x-scissor
move_404.description:
The user slashes at
the foe by crossing
its scythes or claws
as if they were a pair
of scissors.

move_405.name: bug-buzz
move_405.description:
The user vibrates its
wings to generate a
damaging sound wave.
It may also lower the
foe’s Sp. Def stat.

move_406.name: dragon-pulse
move_406.description:
The foe is attacked
with a shock wave
generated by the
user’s gaping mouth.

move_407.name: dragon-rush
move_407.description:
The user tackles the
foe while exhibiting
overwhelming menace.
It may also make the
target flinch.

move_408.name: power-gem
move_408.description:
The user attacks with
a ray of light that
sparkles as if it were
made of gemstones.

move_409.name: drain-punch
move_409.description:
An energy-draining
punch. The user’s
HP is restored by
half the damage taken
by the target.

move_410.name: vacuum-wave
move_410.description:
The user whirls its
fists to send a wave
of pure vacuum at
the foe. This move
always goes first.

move_411.name: focus-blast
move_411.description:
The user heightens
its mental focus and
unleashes its power.
It may also lower the
target’s Sp. Def.

move_412.name: energy-ball
move_412.description:
The user draws power
from nature and
fires it at the foe.
It may also lower the
target’s Sp. Def.

move_413.name: brave-bird
move_413.description:
The user tucks in
its wings and charges
from a low altitude.
The user also takes
serious damage.

move_414.name: earth-power
move_414.description:
The user makes the
ground under the foe
erupt with power.
It may also lower the
target’s Sp. Def.

move_415.name: switcheroo
move_415.description:
The user trades held
items with the foe
faster than the eye
can follow.

move_416.name: giga-impact
move_416.description:
The user charges at
the foe using every
bit of its power.
The user must rest
on the next turn.

move_417.name: nasty-plot
move_417.description:
The user stimulates
its brain by thinking
bad thoughts.
It sharply raises the
user’s Sp. Atk.

move_418.name: bullet-punch
move_418.description:
The user strikes
with a tough punch as
fast as a bullet.
This move always goes
first.

move_419.name: avalanche
move_419.description:
An attack move that
inflicts double the
damage if the user
has been hurt by the
foe in the same turn.

move_420.name: ice-shard
move_420.description:
The user flash
freezes chunks of
ice and hurls them.
This move always goes
first.

move_421.name: shadow-claw
move_421.description:
The user slashes with
a sharp claw made
from shadows.
It has a high
critical-hit ratio.

move_422.name: thunder-fang
move_422.description:
The user bites with
electrified fangs.
It may also make the
foe flinch or become
paralyzed.

move_423.name: ice-fang
move_423.description:
The user bites with
cold-infused fangs.
It may also make the
foe flinch or freeze.

move_424.name: fire-fang
move_424.description:
The user bites with
flame-cloaked fangs.
It may also make the
foe flinch or sustain
a burn.

move_425.name: shadow-sneak
move_425.description:
The user extends its
shadow and attacks
the foe from behind.
This move always goes
first.

move_426.name: mud-bomb
move_426.description:
The user launches a
hard-packed mud ball
to attack.
It may also lower the
target’s accuracy.

move_427.name: psycho-cut
move_427.description:
The user tears at
the foe with blades
formed by psychic
power. It has a high
critical-hit ratio.

move_428.name: zen-headbutt
move_428.description:
The user focuses its
willpower to its head
and rams the foe.
It may also make the
target flinch.

move_429.name: mirror-shot
move_429.description:
The user looses a
flash of energy from
its polished body.
It may also lower the
target’s accuracy.

move_430.name: flash-cannon
move_430.description:
The user gathers all
its light energy and
releases it at once.
It may also lower the
foe’s Sp. Def stat.

move_431.name: rock-climb
move_431.description:
A charging attack
that may also leave
the foe confused.
It can also be used
to scale rocky walls.

move_432.name: defog
move_432.description:
Obstacles are moved,
reducing the foe’s
evasion stat. It can
also be used to
clear deep fog, etc.

move_433.name: trick-room
move_433.description:
The user creates a
bizarre area in which
slower Pokémon get
to move first for five
turns.

move_434.name: draco-meteor
move_434.description:
Comets are summoned
down from the sky.
The attack’s recoil
sharply reduces the
user’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_435.name: discharge
move_435.description:
A flare of electricity
is loosed to strike
all Pokémon in battle.
It may also cause
paralysis.

move_436.name: lava-plume
move_436.description:
An inferno of scarlet
flames washes over
all Pokémon in battle.
It may also inflict
burns.

move_437.name: leaf-storm
move_437.description:
A storm of sharp
leaves is whipped up.
The attack’s recoil
sharply reduces the
user’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_438.name: power-whip
move_438.description:
The user violently
whirls its vines or
tentacles to harshly
lash the foe.

move_439.name: rock-wrecker
move_439.description:
The user launches a
huge boulder at the
foe to attack.
It must rest on the
next turn, however.

move_440.name: cross-poison
move_440.description:
A slashing attack
that may also leave
the target poisoned.
It has a high
critical-hit ratio.

move_441.name: gunk-shot
move_441.description:
The user shoots
filthy garbage at the
foe to attack.
It may also poison
the target.

move_442.name: iron-head
move_442.description:
The foe slams the
target with its
steel-hard head.
It may also make the
target flinch.

move_443.name: magnet-bomb
move_443.description:
The user launches a
steel bomb that
sticks to the target.
This attack will not
miss.

move_444.name: stone-edge
move_444.description:
The user stabs the
foe with a sharpened
stone. It has a high
critical-hit ratio.

move_445.name: captivate
move_445.description:
If it is the opposite
gender of the user,
the foe is charmed
into sharply lowering
its Sp. Atk stat.

move_446.name: stealth-rock
move_446.description:
The user lays a trap
of levitating stones
around the foe. The
trap hurts foes that
switch into battle.

move_447.name: grass-knot
move_447.description:
The user snares the
foe with grass and
trips it. The heavier
the foe, the greater
the damage.

move_448.name: chatter
move_448.description:
The user attacks
using a sound wave
based on words it has
learned. It may also
confuse the foe.

move_449.name: judgment
move_449.description:
The user releases
countless shots of
light. Its type varies
with the kind of Plate
the user is holding.

move_450.name: bug-bite
move_450.description:
The user bites the
foe. If the foe is
holding a Berry, the
user eats it and
gains its effect.

move_451.name: charge-beam
move_451.description:
The user fires a
concentrated bundle
of electricity. It may
also raise the user’s
Sp. Atk stat.

move_452.name: wood-hammer
move_452.description:
The user slams its
rugged body into the
foe to attack. The
user also sustains
serious damage.

move_453.name: aqua-jet
move_453.description:
The user lunges at
the foe at a speed
that makes it almost
invisible. It is sure
to strike first.

move_454.name: attack-order
move_454.description:
The user calls out
its underlings to
pummel the foe.
It has a high
critical-hit ratio.

move_455.name: defend-order
move_455.description:
The user calls out
its underlings to
make a living shield,
raising its Defense
and Sp. Def stats.

move_456.name: heal-order
move_456.description:
The user calls out
its underlings to heal
it. The user regains
up to half of its
max HP.

move_457.name: head-smash
move_457.description:
The user delivers a
life-endangering head
butt at full power.
The user also takes
terrible damage.

move_458.name: double-hit
move_458.description:
The user slams the
foe with a tail, etc.
The target is hit
twice in a row.

move_459.name: roar-of-time
move_459.description:
The user blasts the
foe with power that
distorts even time.
The user must rest
on the next turn.

move_460.name: spacial-rend
move_460.description:
The user tears the
foe along with the
space around it.
This move has a high
critical-hit ratio.

move_461.name: lunar-dance
move_461.description:
The user faints. In
return, the Pokémon
taking its place will
have its status and
HP fully restored.

move_462.name: crush-grip
move_462.description:
The foe is crushed
with great force.
The attack is more
powerful the more HP
the foe has left.

move_463.name: magma-storm
move_463.description:
The foe becomes
trapped within a
maelstrom of fire
that rages for two
to five turns.

move_464.name: dark-void
move_464.description:
The foe is dragged
into a world of total
darkness that puts it
to sleep.

move_465.name: seed-flare
move_465.description:
The user generates
a shock wave from
within its body.
It may also lower the
target’s Sp. Def.

move_466.name: ominous-wind
move_466.description:
The user creates a
gust of repulsive
wind. It may also
raise all the user’s
stats at once.

move_467.name: shadow-force
move_467.description:
The user disappears,
then strikes the foe
on the second turn.
It hits even if the
foe used Protect.

move_468.name: hone-claws
move_468.description:
The user sharpens its claws to
boost its Attack stat and accuracy.

move_469.name: wide-guard
move_469.description:
The user and its allies are protected from
wide-ranging attacks for one turn. If used
in succession, its chance of failing rises.

move_470.name: guard-split
move_470.description:
The user employs its psychic power to
average its Defense and Sp. Def stats
with those of its target’s.

move_471.name: power-split
move_471.description:
The user employs its psychic power to
average its Attack and Sp. Atk stats
with those of the target’s.

move_472.name: wonder-room
move_472.description:
The user creates a bizarre area in which
Pokémon’s Defense and Sp. Def
stats are swapped for five turns.

move_473.name: psyshock
move_473.description:
The user materializes an odd
psychic wave to attack the target.
This attack does physical damage.

move_474.name: venoshock
move_474.description:
The user drenches the target in a special
poisonous liquid. Its power is doubled
if the target is poisoned.

move_475.name: autotomize
move_475.description:
The user sheds part of its body
to make itself lighter and sharply
raise its Speed stat.

move_476.name: rage-powder
move_476.description:
The user scatters a cloud of irritating
powder to draw attention to itself.
Opponents aim only at the user.

move_477.name: telekinesis
move_477.description:
The user makes the target float with its
psychic power. The target is easier to
hit for three turns.

move_478.name: magic-room
move_478.description:
The user creates a bizarre area
in which Pokémon’s held items
lose their effects for five turns.

move_479.name: smack-down
move_479.description:
The user throws a stone or projectile to
attack an opponent. A flying Pokémon will
fall to the ground when hit.

move_480.name: storm-throw
move_480.description:
The user strikes the target with a fierce
blow. This attack always results in a
critical hit.

move_481.name: flame-burst
move_481.description:
The user attacks the target with a
bursting flame. The bursting flame damages
Pokémon next to the target as well.

move_482.name: sludge-wave
move_482.description:
It swamps the area around the user with a
giant sludge wave.
It may also poison those hit.

move_483.name: quiver-dance
move_483.description:
The user lightly performs a beautiful,
mystic dance. It boosts the user’s
Sp. Atk, Sp. Def, and Speed stats.

move_484.name: heavy-slam
move_484.description:
The user slams into the target with its
heavy body. The more the user outweighs
the target, the greater its damage.

move_485.name: synchronoise
move_485.description:
Using an odd shock wave, the user
inflicts damage on any Pokémon of the same
type in the area around it.

move_486.name: electro-ball
move_486.description:
The user hurls an electric orb
at the target. The faster the user is
than the target, the greater the damage.

move_487.name: soak
move_487.description:
The user shoots a torrent of water
at the target and changes
the target’s type to Water.

move_488.name: flame-charge
move_488.description:
The user cloaks itself with flame and
attacks. Building up more power,
it raises the user’s Speed stat.

move_489.name: coil
move_489.description:
The user coils up and concentrates.
This raises its Attack and Defense stats
as well as its accuracy.

move_490.name: low-sweep
move_490.description:
The user attacks the target’s legs
swiftly, reducing the target’s
Speed stat.

move_491.name: acid-spray
move_491.description:
The user spits fluid that works to melt
the target. This harshly reduces
the target’s Sp. Def stat.

move_492.name: foul-play
move_492.description:
The user turns the target’s power
against it. The higher the target’s
Attack stat, the greater the damage.

move_493.name: simple-beam
move_493.description:
The user’s mysterious psychic wave
changes the target’s Ability to Simple.

move_494.name: entrainment
move_494.description:
The user dances with an odd rhythm that
compels the target to mimic it, making the
target’s Ability the same as the user’s.

move_495.name: after-you
move_495.description:
The user helps the target and makes it
use its move right after the user.

move_496.name: round
move_496.description:
The user attacks the target with a song.
Others can join in the Round and make
the attack do greater damage.

move_497.name: echoed-voice
move_497.description:
The user attacks the target with an
echoing voice. If this move is used
every turn, it does greater damage.

move_498.name: chip-away
move_498.description:
Looking for an opening, the user strikes
continually. The target’s stat changes
don’t affect this attack’s damage.

move_499.name: clear-smog
move_499.description:
The user attacks by throwing a clump of
special mud. All status changes are
returned to normal.

move_500.name: stored-power
move_500.description:
The user attacks the target with stored
power. The more the user’s stats are
raised, the greater the damage.

move_501.name: quick-guard
move_501.description:
The user protects itself and its allies
from priority moves. If used in
succession, its chance of failing rises.

move_502.name: ally-switch
move_502.description:
The user teleports using a strange power
and switches its place with one of
its allies.

move_503.name: scald
move_503.description:
The user shoots boiling hot water at
its target. It may also leave the target
with a burn.

move_504.name: shell-smash
move_504.description:
The user breaks its shell, lowering its
Defense and Sp. Def stats but sharply
raising Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats.

move_505.name: heal-pulse
move_505.description:
The user emits a healing pulse which
restores the target’s HP by up to
half of its max HP.

move_506.name: hex
move_506.description:
This relentless attack does massive
damage to a target affected
by status problems.

move_507.name: sky-drop
move_507.description:
The user takes the target into the sky,
then drops it during the next turn.
The target cannot attack while in the sky.

move_508.name: shift-gear
move_508.description:
The user rotates its gears, raising its
Attack and sharply raising its Speed.

move_509.name: circle-throw
move_509.description:
The user throws the target and drags out
another Pokémon in its party.
In the wild, the battle ends.

move_510.name: incinerate
move_510.description:
The user attacks the target with fire.
If the target is holding a Berry, the
Berry becomes burnt up and unusable.

move_511.name: quash
move_511.description:
The user suppresses the target and
makes its move go last.

move_512.name: acrobatics
move_512.description:
The user nimbly strikes the target.
If the user is not holding an item,
this attack inflicts massive damage.

move_513.name: reflect-type
move_513.description:
The user reflects the target’s type,
making it the same type as the target.

move_514.name: retaliate
move_514.description:
The user gets revenge for a fainted ally.
If an ally fainted in the previous turn,
this attack’s damage increases.

move_515.name: final-gambit
move_515.description:
The user risks everything to attack its
target. The user faints but does damage
equal to the user’s HP.

move_516.name: bestow
move_516.description:
The user passes its held item to the
target when the target isn’t holding
an item.

move_517.name: inferno
move_517.description:
The user attacks by engulfing the target
in an intense fire. It leaves the target
with a burn.

move_518.name: water-pledge
move_518.description:
A column of water strikes the target. When
combined with its fire equivalent, the
damage increases and a rainbow appears.

move_519.name: fire-pledge
move_519.description:
A column of fire hits opposing Pokémon.
When used with its Grass equivalent, its
damage increases into a vast sea of fire.

move_520.name: grass-pledge
move_520.description:
A column of grass hits opposing Pokémon.
When used with its water equivalent, its
damage increases into a vast swamp.

move_521.name: volt-switch
move_521.description:
After making its attack, the user
rushes back to switch places with
a party Pokémon in waiting.

move_522.name: struggle-bug
move_522.description:
While resisting, the user attacks the
opposing Pokémon. The targets’
Sp. Atk stat is reduced.

move_523.name: bulldoze
move_523.description:
The user stomps down on the ground
and attacks everything in the area. Hit
Pokémon’s Speed stat is reduced.

move_524.name: frost-breath
move_524.description:
The user blows a cold breath on the
target. This attack always results in
a critical hit.

move_525.name: dragon-tail
move_525.description:
The user knocks away the target and
drags out another Pokémon in its party.
In the wild, the battle ends.

move_526.name: work-up
move_526.description:
The user is roused, and its Attack
and Sp. Atk stats increase.

move_527.name: electroweb
move_527.description:
The user captures and attacks opposing
Pokémon by using an electric net. It
reduces the targets’ Speed stat.

move_528.name: wild-charge
move_528.description:
The user shrouds itself in electricity
and smashes into its target.
It also damages the user a little.

move_529.name: drill-run
move_529.description:
The user crashes into its target while
rotating its body like a drill.
Critical hits land more easily.

move_530.name: dual-chop
move_530.description:
The user attacks its target by hitting
it with brutal strikes.
The target is hit twice in a row.

move_531.name: heart-stamp
move_531.description:
The user unleashes a vicious blow after
its cute act makes the target less wary.
It may also make the target flinch.

move_532.name: horn-leech
move_532.description:
The user drains the target’s energy with
its horns. The user’s HP is restored
by half the damage taken by the target.

move_533.name: sacred-sword
move_533.description:
The user attacks by slicing with its long
horns. The target’s stat changes
don’t affect this attack’s damage.

move_534.name: razor-shell
move_534.description:
The user cuts its target with sharp
shells. This attack may also lower the
target’s Defense stat.

move_535.name: heat-crash
move_535.description:
The user slams its target with its flame-
covered body. The more the user outweighs
the target, the greater the damage.

move_536.name: leaf-tornado
move_536.description:
The user attacks its target by
encircling it in sharp leaves. This attack
may also lower the target’s accuracy.

move_537.name: steamroller
move_537.description:
The user crushes its targets by rolling
over them with its rolled-up body.
This attack may make the target flinch.

move_538.name: cotton-guard
move_538.description:
The user protects itself by wrapping
its body in soft cotton, drastically
raising the user’s Defense stat.

move_539.name: night-daze
move_539.description:
The user lets loose a pitch-black shock
wave at its target. It may also lower the
target’s accuracy.

move_540.name: psystrike
move_540.description:
The user materializes an odd
psychic wave to attack the target.
This attack does physical damage.

move_541.name: tail-slap
move_541.description:
The user attacks by striking the target
with its hard tail. It hits the target two
to five times in a row.

move_542.name: hurricane
move_542.description:
The user attacks by wrapping its opponent
in a fierce wind that flies up into the sky.
It may also confuse the target.

move_543.name: head-charge
move_543.description:
The user charges its head into its
target, using its powerful guard hair.
It also damages the user a little.

move_544.name: gear-grind
move_544.description:
The user attacks by throwing
two steel gears at its target.

move_545.name: searing-shot
move_545.description:
An inferno of scarlet flames torches
everything around the user. It may
leave targets with a burn.

move_546.name: techno-blast
move_546.description:
The user fires a beam of light at
its target. The type changes depending
on the Drive the user holds.

move_547.name: relic-song
move_547.description:
The user sings an ancient song and attacks
by appealing to the hearts of those
listening. It may also induce sleep.

move_548.name: secret-sword
move_548.description:
The user cuts with its long horn. The odd
power contained in the horn does physical
damage to the target.

move_549.name: glaciate
move_549.description:
The user attacks by blowing freezing cold
air at opposing Pokémon. This attack
reduces the targets’ Speed stat.

move_550.name: bolt-strike
move_550.description:
The user charges its target, surrounding
itself with a great amount of electricity.
It may leave the target with paralysis.

move_551.name: blue-flare
move_551.description:
The user attacks by engulfing the target
in an intense, yet beautiful, blue flame.
It may leave the target with a burn.

move_552.name: fiery-dance
move_552.description:
Cloaked in flames, the user dances
and flaps its wings. It may also
raise the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_553.name: freeze-shock
move_553.description:
On the second turn, the user hits the
target with electrically charged ice.
It may leave the target with paralysis.

move_554.name: ice-burn
move_554.description:
On the second turn, an ultracold,
freezing wind surrounds the target.
This may leave the target with a burn.

move_555.name: snarl
move_555.description:
The user yells as if it is ranting about
something, making the target’s Sp. Atk
stat decrease.

move_556.name: icicle-crash
move_556.description:
The user attacks by harshly dropping
an icicle onto the target.
It may also make the target flinch.

move_557.name: v-create
move_557.description:
With a hot flame on its forehead, the user
hurls itself at its target. It lowers the
user’s Defense, Sp. Def, and Speed stats.

move_558.name: fusion-flare
move_558.description:
The user brings down a giant flame.
This attack does greater damage when
influenced by an enormous thunderbolt.

move_559.name: fusion-bolt
move_559.description:
The user throws down a giant thunderbolt.
This attack does greater damage
when influenced by an enormous flame.

move_560.name: flying-press
move_560.description:
The user dives down onto the target
from the sky. This move is Fighting
and Flying type simultaneously.

move_561.name: mat-block
move_561.description:
Using a pulled-up mat as a shield, the user
protects itself and its allies from damaging moves.
This does not stop status moves.

move_562.name: belch
move_562.description:
The user lets out a damaging belch
at the target. The user must eat a held
Berry to use this move.

move_563.name: rototiller
move_563.description:
Tilling the soil, the user makes it easier
for plants to grow. This raises the Attack
and Sp. Atk stats of Grass-type Pokémon.

move_564.name: sticky-web
move_564.description:
The user weaves a sticky net around
the opposing team, which lowers their
Speed stat upon switching into battle.

move_565.name: fell-stinger
move_565.description:
When the user knocks out a target
with this move, the user’s Attack stat
rises sharply.

move_566.name: phantom-force
move_566.description:
The user vanishes somewhere, then strikes
the target on the next turn.
This move hits even if the target protects itself.

move_567.name: trick-or-treat
move_567.description:
The user takes the target trick-or-treating.
This adds Ghost type to the target’s type.

move_568.name: noble-roar
move_568.description:
Letting out a noble roar, the user
intimidates the target and lowers
its Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

move_569.name: ion-deluge
move_569.description:
The user disperses electrically charged
particles, which changes Normal-type
moves to Electric-type moves.

move_570.name: parabolic-charge
move_570.description:
The user attacks everything around it.
The user’s HP is restored by half
the damage taken by those hit.

move_571.name: forests-curse
move_571.description:
The user puts a forest curse on the target.
Afflicted targets are now Grass type as well.

move_572.name: petal-blizzard
move_572.description:
The user stirs up a violent petal blizzard
and attacks everything around it.

move_573.name: freeze-dry
move_573.description:
The user rapidly cools the target.
This may also leave the target frozen.
This move is super effective on Water types.

move_574.name: disarming-voice
move_574.description:
Letting out a charming cry, the user does
emotional damage to opposing Pokémon.
This attack never misses.

move_575.name: parting-shot
move_575.description:
With a parting threat, the user lowers
the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk stats.
Then it switches with a party Pokémon.

move_576.name: topsy-turvy
move_576.description:
All stat changes affecting the target
turn topsy-turvy and become the
opposite of what they were.

move_577.name: draining-kiss
move_577.description:
The user steals the target’s energy with a kiss.
The user’s HP is restored by over half
of the damage taken by the target.

move_578.name: crafty-shield
move_578.description:
The user protects itself and its allies from
status moves with a mysterious power.
This does not stop moves that do damage.

move_579.name: flower-shield
move_579.description:
The user raises the Defense stat
of all Grass-type Pokémon in battle
with a mysterious power.

move_580.name: grassy-terrain
move_580.description:
The user turns the ground under everyone’s feet
to grass for five turns. This restores the HP of
Pokémon on the ground a little every turn.

move_581.name: misty-terrain
move_581.description:
The user covers the ground under everyone’s feet
with mist for five turns. This protects Pokémon
on the ground from status conditions.

move_582.name: electrify
move_582.description:
If the target is electrified before it uses
a move during that turn, the target’s
move becomes Electric type.

move_583.name: play-rough
move_583.description:
The user plays rough with the target
and attacks it. This may also lower
the target’s Attack stat.

move_584.name: fairy-wind
move_584.description:
The user stirs up a fairy wind
and strikes the target with it.

move_585.name: moonblast
move_585.description:
Borrowing the power of the moon,
the user attacks the target.
This may also lower the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_586.name: boomburst
move_586.description:
The user attacks everything around it
with the destructive power of a terrible,
explosive sound.

move_587.name: fairy-lock
move_587.description:
By locking down the battlefield,
the user keeps all Pokémon from
fleeing during the next turn.

move_588.name: kings-shield
move_588.description:
The user takes a defensive stance while it protects
itself from damage. It also harshly lowers the Attack
stat of any attacker who makes direct contact.

move_589.name: play-nice
move_589.description:
The user and the target become friends,
and the target loses its will to fight.
This lowers the target’s Attack stat.

move_590.name: confide
move_590.description:
The user tells the target a secret, and the target
loses its ability to concentrate. This lowers
the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_591.name: diamond-storm
move_591.description:
The user whips up a storm of diamonds
to damage opposing Pokémon. This may
also raise the user’s Defense stat.

move_592.name: steam-eruption
move_592.description:
The user immerses the target in superheated steam.
This may also leave the target with a burn.

move_593.name: hyperspace-hole
move_593.description:
Using a hyperspace hole, the user appears
right next to the target and strikes. This
also hits a target using Protect or Detect.

move_594.name: water-shuriken
move_594.description:
The user hits the target with throwing
stars two to five times in a row.
This move always goes first.

move_595.name: mystical-fire
move_595.description:
The user attacks by breathing
a special, hot fire. This also
lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_596.name: spiky-shield
move_596.description:
In addition to protecting the user from attacks,
this move also damages any attacker who
makes direct contact.

move_597.name: aromatic-mist
move_597.description:
The user raises the Sp. Def stat of an ally
Pokémon by using a mysterious aroma.

move_598.name: eerie-impulse
move_598.description:
The user’s body generates an eerie impulse.
Exposing the target to it harshly lowers
the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_599.name: venom-drench
move_599.description:
Opposing Pokémon are drenched in an odd
poisonous liquid. This lowers the Attack,
Sp. Atk, and Speed stats of a poisoned target.

move_600.name: powder
move_600.description:
The user covers the target in a powder
that explodes and damages the target
if it uses a Fire-type move.

move_601.name: geomancy
move_601.description:
The user absorbs energy and sharply raises
its Sp. Atk, Sp. Def, and Speed stats
on the next turn.

move_602.name: magnetic-flux
move_602.description:
The user manipulates magnetic fields,
which raises the Defense and Sp. Def stats
of ally Pokémon with the Plus or Minus Ability.

move_603.name: happy-hour
move_603.description:
Using Happy Hour doubles
the amount of prize money
received after battle.

move_604.name: electric-terrain
move_604.description:
The user electrifies the ground under
everyone’s feet for five turns.
Pokémon on the ground no longer fall asleep.

move_605.name: dazzling-gleam
move_605.description:
The user damages opposing Pokémon
by emitting a powerful flash.

move_606.name: celebrate
move_606.description:
The Pokémon congratulates
you on your special day!

move_607.name: hold-hands
move_607.description:
The user and an ally hold hands.
This makes them very happy.

move_608.name: baby-doll-eyes
move_608.description:
The user stares at the target with its baby-doll
eyes, which lowers its Attack stat. This move
always goes first.

move_609.name: nuzzle
move_609.description:
The user attacks by nuzzling its electrified
cheeks against the target. This also leaves
the target with paralysis.

move_610.name: hold-back
move_610.description:
The user holds back when it attacks
and the target is left with at least 1 HP.

move_611.name: infestation
move_611.description:
The target is infested and attacked for
four to five turns.
The target can’t flee during this time.

move_612.name: power-up-punch
move_612.description:
Striking opponents over and over makes
the user’s fists harder.
Hitting a target raises the Attack stat.

move_613.name: oblivion-wing
move_613.description:
The user absorbs its target’s HP.
The user’s HP is restored by over half
of the damage taken by the target.

move_614.name: thousand-arrows
move_614.description:
This move also hits opposing Pokémon
that are in the air. Those Pokémon are
knocked down to the ground.

move_615.name: thousand-waves
move_615.description:
The user attacks with a wave
that crawls along the ground.
Those hit can’t flee from battle.

move_616.name: lands-wrath
move_616.description:
The user gathers the energy of the land
and focuses that power on opposing
Pokémon to damage them.

move_617.name: light-of-ruin
move_617.description:
Drawing power from the Eternal Flower,
the user fires a powerful beam of light.
This also damages the user quite a lot.

move_618.name: origin-pulse
move_618.description:
The user attacks opposing Pokémon with countless
beams of light that glow a deep and brilliant blue.

move_619.name: precipice-blades
move_619.description:
The user attacks opposing Pokémon by manifesting
the power of the land in fearsome blades of stone.

move_620.name: dragon-ascent
move_620.description:
After soaring upward, the user attacks its target by
dropping out of the sky at high speeds, although it
lowers its own Defense and Sp. Def in the process.

move_621.name: hyperspace-fury
move_621.description:
Using its many arms, the user unleashes a barrage of
attacks that ignore the effects of moves like Protect
and Detect. This attack lowers the user’s Defense.

move_622.name: breakneck-blitz--physical
move_622.description:
The user builds up its momentum using its Z-Power
and crashes into the target at full speed. The power
varies, depending on the original move.

move_624.name: all-out-pummeling--physical
move_624.description:
The user rams an energy orb created by its Z-Power
into the target with full force. The power varies,
depending on the original move.

move_626.name: supersonic-skystrike--physical
move_626.description:
The user soars up with its Z-Power and plummets
toward the target at full speed. The power varies,
depending on the original move.

move_628.name: acid-downpour--physical
move_628.description:
The user creates a poisonous swamp using its
Z-Power and sinks the target into it at full force.
The power varies, depending on the original move.

move_630.name: tectonic-rage--physical
move_630.description:
The user burrows deep into the ground and slams
into the target with the full force of its Z-Power.
The power varies, depending on the original move.

move_632.name: continental-crush--physical
move_632.description:
The user summons a huge rock mountain using its
Z-Power and drops it onto the target with full force.
The power varies, depending on the original move.

move_634.name: savage-spin-out--physical
move_634.description:
The user binds the target with full force with
threads of silk that the user spits using its Z-Power.
The power varies, depending on the original move.

move_636.name: never-ending-nightmare--physical
move_636.description:
Deep-seated grudges summoned by the user’s
Z-Power trap the target. The power varies,
depending on the original move.

move_638.name: corkscrew-crash--physical
move_638.description:
The user spins very fast and rams into the target
with the full force of its Z-Power. The power varies,
depending on the original move.

move_640.name: inferno-overdrive--physical
move_640.description:
The user breathes a stream of intense fire toward
the target with the full force of its Z-Power.
The power varies depending on the original move.

move_642.name: hydro-vortex--physical
move_642.description:
The user creates a huge whirling current using
its Z-Power to swallow the target with full force.
The power varies, depending on the original move.

move_644.name: bloom-doom--physical
move_644.description:
The user collects energy from plants using its
Z-Power and attacks the target with full force.
The power varies, depending on the original move.

move_646.name: gigavolt-havoc--physical
move_646.description:
The user hits the target with a powerful electric
current collected by its Z-Power. The power varies,
depending on the original move.

move_648.name: shattered-psyche--physical
move_648.description:
The user controls the target with its Z-Power and
hurts the target with full force. The power varies,
depending on the original move.

move_650.name: subzero-slammer--physical
move_650.description:
The user dramatically drops the temperature using
its Z-Power and freezes the target with full force.
The power varies, depending on the original move.

move_652.name: devastating-drake--physical
move_652.description:
The user materializes its aura using its Z-Power and
attacks the target with full force. The power varies,
depending on the original move.

move_654.name: black-hole-eclipse--physical
move_654.description:
The user gathers dark energy using its Z-Power
and sucks the target into it. The power varies,
depending on the original move.

move_656.name: twinkle-tackle--physical
move_656.description:
The user creates a very charming space using its
Z-Power and totally toys with the target. The power
varies, depending on the original move.

move_658.name: catastropika
move_658.description:
The user, Pikachu, surrounds itself with the
maximum amount of electricity using its Z-Power
and pounces on its target with full force.

move_659.name: shore-up
move_659.description:
The user regains up to half of its max HP. It restores
more HP in a sandstorm.

move_660.name: first-impression
move_660.description:
Although this move has great power, it only works
the first turn the user is in battle.

move_661.name: baneful-bunker
move_661.description:
In addition to protecting the user from attacks, this
move also poisons any attacker that makes
direct contact.

move_662.name: spirit-shackle
move_662.description:
The user attacks while simultaneously stitching the
target’s shadow to the ground to prevent the target
from escaping.

move_663.name: darkest-lariat
move_663.description:
The user swings both arms and hits the target.
The target’s stat changes don’t affect this
attack’s damage.

move_664.name: sparkling-aria
move_664.description:
The user bursts into song, emitting many bubbles.
Any Pokémon suffering from a burn will be healed
by the touch of these bubbles.

move_665.name: ice-hammer
move_665.description:
The user swings and hits with its strong, heavy fist.
It lowers the user’s Speed, however.

move_666.name: floral-healing
move_666.description:
The user restores the target’s HP by up to half of its
max HP. It restores more HP when the terrain
is grass.

move_667.name: high-horsepower
move_667.description:
The user fiercely attacks the target using its
entire body.

move_668.name: strength-sap
move_668.description:
The user restores its HP by the same amount as the
target’s Attack stat. It also lowers the target’s
Attack stat.

move_669.name: solar-blade
move_669.description:
In this two-turn attack, the user gathers light and
fills a blade with the light’s energy, attacking the
target on the next turn.

move_670.name: leafage
move_670.description: The user attacks by pelting the target with leaves.

move_671.name: spotlight
move_671.description:
The user shines a spotlight on the target so that
only the target will be attacked during the turn.

move_672.name: toxic-thread
move_672.description:
The user shoots poisonous threads to poison the
target and lower the target’s Speed stat.

move_673.name: laser-focus
move_673.description:
The user concentrates intensely. The attack on the
next turn always results in a critical hit.

move_674.name: gear-up
move_674.description:
The user engages its gears to raise the Attack and
Sp. Atk stats of ally Pokémon with the Plus or
Minus Ability.

move_675.name: throat-chop
move_675.description:
The user attacks the target’s throat, and the
resultant suffering prevents the target from using
moves that emit sound for two turns.

move_676.name: pollen-puff
move_676.description:
The user attacks the enemy with a pollen puff that
explodes. If the target is an ally, it gives the ally a
pollen puff that restores its HP instead.

move_677.name: anchor-shot
move_677.description:
The user entangles the target with its anchor chain
while attacking. The target becomes unable to flee.

move_678.name: psychic-terrain
move_678.description:
This protects Pokémon on the ground from priority
moves and powers up Psychic-type moves for
five turns.

move_679.name: lunge
move_679.description:
The user makes a lunge at the target, attacking with
full force. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

move_680.name: fire-lash
move_680.description:
The user strikes the target with a burning lash. This
also lowers the target’s Defense stat.

move_681.name: power-trip
move_681.description:
The user boasts its strength and attacks the target.
The more the user’s stats are raised, the greater the
move’s power.

move_682.name: burn-up
move_682.description:
To inflict massive damage, the user burns itself out.
After using this move, the user will no longer be
Fire type.

move_683.name: speed-swap
move_683.description: The user exchanges Speed stats with the target.

move_684.name: smart-strike
move_684.description:
The user stabs the target with a sharp horn. This
attack never misses.

move_685.name: purify
move_685.description:
The user heals the target’s status condition. If the
move succeeds, it also restores the user’s own HP.

move_686.name: revelation-dance
move_686.description:
The user attacks the target by dancing very hard.
The user’s type determines the type of this move.

move_687.name: core-enforcer
move_687.description:
If the Pokémon the user has inflicted damage on
have already used their moves, this move eliminates
the effect of the target’s Ability.

move_688.name: trop-kick
move_688.description:
The user lands an intense kick of tropical origins on
the target. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

move_689.name: instruct
move_689.description:
The user instructs the target to use the target’s last
move again.

move_690.name: beak-blast
move_690.description:
The user first heats up its beak, and then it attacks
the target. Making direct contact with the Pokémon
while it’s heating up its beak results in a burn.

move_691.name: clanging-scales
move_691.description:
The user rubs the scales on its entire body and
makes a huge noise to attack the opposing Pokémon.
The user’s Defense stat goes down after the attack.

move_692.name: dragon-hammer
move_692.description:
The user uses its body like a hammer to attack the
target and inflict damage.

move_693.name: brutal-swing
move_693.description:
The user swings its body around violently to inflict
damage on everything in its vicinity.

move_694.name: aurora-veil
move_694.description:
This move reduces damage from physical and
special moves for five turns. This can be used only
in a hailstorm.

move_695.name: sinister-arrow-raid
move_695.description:
The user, Decidueye, creates countless arrows
using its Z-Power and shoots the target with
full force.

move_696.name: malicious-moonsault
move_696.description:
The user, Incineroar, strengthens its body using
its Z-Power and crashes into the target with
full force.

move_697.name: oceanic-operetta
move_697.description:
The user, Primarina, summons a massive amount of 
water using its Z-Power and attacks the target with 
full force.

move_698.name: guardian-of-alola
move_698.description:
The user, the Land Spirit Pokémon, obtains Alola’s
energy using its Z-Power and attacks the target with
full force. This reduces the target’s HP greatly.

move_699.name: soul-stealing-7-star-strike
move_699.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Marshadow,
punches and kicks the target consecutively
with full force.

move_700.name: stoked-sparksurfer
move_700.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Alolan Raichu,
attacks the target with full force. This move leaves
the target with paralysis.

move_701.name: pulverizing-pancake
move_701.description:
Z-Power brings out the true capabilities of the user,
Snorlax. The Pokémon moves its enormous body
energetically and attacks the target with full force.

move_702.name: extreme-evoboost
move_702.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Eevee, gets
energy from its evolved friends and boosts its
stats sharply.

move_703.name: genesis-supernova
move_703.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Mew, attacks
the target with full force. The terrain will be charged
with psychic energy.

move_704.name: shell-trap
move_704.description:
The user sets a shell trap. If the user is hit by a
physical move, the trap will explode and inflict
damage on the opposing Pokémon.

move_705.name: fleur-cannon
move_705.description:
The user unleashes a strong beam. The attack’s
recoil harshly lowers the user’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_706.name: psychic-fangs
move_706.description:
The user bites the target with its psychic
capabilities. This can also destroy Light Screen
and Reflect.

move_707.name: stomping-tantrum
move_707.description:
Driven by frustration, the user attacks the target. If
the user’s previous move has failed, the power of
this move doubles.

move_708.name: shadow-bone
move_708.description:
The user attacks by beating the target with a
bone that contains a spirit. This may also lower
the target’s Defense stat.

move_709.name: accelerock
move_709.description:
The user smashes into the target at high speed.
This move always goes first.

move_710.name: liquidation
move_710.description:
The user slams into the target using a full-force
blast of water. This may also lower the target’s
Defense stat.

move_711.name: prismatic-laser
move_711.description:
The user shoots powerful lasers using the power of
a prism. The user can’t move on the next turn.

move_712.name: spectral-thief
move_712.description:
The user hides in the target’s shadow, steals
the target’s stat boosts, and then attacks.

move_713.name: sunsteel-strike
move_713.description:
The user slams into the target with the force of a
meteor. This move can be used on the target 
regardless of its Abilities.

move_714.name: moongeist-beam
move_714.description:
The user emits a sinister ray to attack the target.
This move can be used on the target regardless of 
its Abilities.

move_715.name: tearful-look
move_715.description:
The user gets teary eyed to make the target lose
its combative spirit. This lowers the target’s
Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

move_716.name: zing-zap
move_716.description:
A strong electric blast crashes down on the target,
giving it an electric shock. This may also make the
target flinch.

move_717.name: natures-madness
move_717.description:
The user hits the target with the force of nature.
It halves the target’s HP.

move_718.name: multi-attack
move_718.description:
Cloaking itself in high energy, the user slams into the
target. The memory held determines the move’s type.

move_719.name: 10-000-000-volt-thunderbolt
move_719.description:
The user, Pikachu wearing a cap, powers up a jolt of
electricity using its Z-Power and unleashes it.
Critical hits land more easily.

move_720.name: mind-blown
move_720.description:
The user attacks everything around it by causing its
own head to explode. This also damages the user.

move_721.name: plasma-fists
move_721.description:
The user attacks with electrically charged fists.
This move changes Normal-type moves to
Electric-type moves.

move_722.name: photon-geyser
move_722.description:
The user attacks a target with a pillar of light. This
move inflicts Attack or Sp. Atk damage—whichever
stat is higher for the user.

move_723.name: light-that-burns-the-sky
move_723.description:
This attack inflicts Attack or Sp. Atk damage—
whichever stat is higher for the user, Necrozma. 
This move ignores the target’s Ability.

move_724.name: searing-sunraze-smash
move_724.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Solgaleo,
attacks the target with full force. This move can
ignore the effect of the target’s Ability.

move_725.name: menacing-moonraze-maelstrom
move_725.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Lunala,
attacks the target with full force. This move can
ignore the effect of the target’s Ability.

move_726.name: lets-snuggle-forever
move_726.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Mimikyu,
punches the target with full force.

move_727.name: splintered-stormshards
move_727.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Lycanroc,
attacks the target with full force. This move negates
the effect on the battlefield.

move_728.name: clangorous-soulblaze
move_728.description:
After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Kommo-o,
attacks the opposing Pokémon with full force. This
move boosts the user’s stats.

move_729.name: zippy-zap
move_729.description:
The user attacks the target with bursts of electricity
at high speed. This move always goes first and results
in a critical hit.

move_730.name: splishy-splash
move_730.description:
The user charges a huge wave with electricity and
hits the opposing Pokémon with the wave. This may
also leave the opposing Pokémon with paralysis.

move_731.name: floaty-fall
move_731.description:
The user floats in the air, and then dives at a steep
angle to attack the target. This may also make the
target flinch.

move_732.name: pika-papow
move_732.description:
The more Pikachu loves its Trainer, the greater the
move’s power. It never misses.

move_733.name: bouncy-bubble
move_733.description:
The user attacks by shooting water bubbles at the
target. It then absorbs water and restores its HP by half
the damage taken by the target.

move_734.name: buzzy-buzz
move_734.description:
The user shoots a jolt of electricity to attack the target.
This also leaves the target with paralysis.

move_735.name: sizzly-slide
move_735.description:
The user cloaks itself in fire and charges at the target.
This also leaves the target with a burn.

move_736.name: glitzy-glow
move_736.description:
The user bombards the target with telekinetic force.
A wondrous wall of light is put up to weaken the power
of the opposing Pokémon’s special moves.

move_737.name: baddy-bad
move_737.description:
The user acts bad and attacks the target.
A wondrous wall of light is put up to weaken the power
of the opposing Pokémon’s physical moves.

move_738.name: sappy-seed
move_738.description:
The user grows a gigantic stalk that scatters seeds
to attack the target. The seeds drain the target’s
HP every turn.

move_739.name: freezy-frost
move_739.description:
The user attacks with a crystal made of cold frozen
haze. It eliminates every stat change among all the
Pokémon engaged in battle.

move_740.name: sparkly-swirl
move_740.description:
The user attacks the target by wrapping it with
a whirlwind of an overpowering scent. This also
heals all status conditions of the user’s party.

move_741.name: veevee-volley
move_741.description:
The more Eevee loves its Trainer, the greater the
move’s power. It never misses.

move_742.name: double-iron-bash
move_742.description:
The user rotates, centering the hex nut in its chest,
and then strikes with its arms twice in a row. This may
also make the target flinch.

move_743.name: max-guard
move_743.description:
This move enables the user to protect itself from
all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used
in succession.

move_744.name: dynamax-cannon
move_744.description:
The user unleashes a strong beam from its core.
This move deals twice the damage if the target
is Dynamaxed.

move_745.name: snipe-shot
move_745.description:
The user ignores the effects of opposing Pokémon’s
moves and Abilities that draw in moves, allowing this
move to hit the chosen target.

move_746.name: jaw-lock
move_746.description:
This move prevents the user and the target from
switching out until either of them faints. The effect goes
away if either of the Pokémon leaves the field.

move_747.name: stuff-cheeks
move_747.description:
The user eats its held Berry, then sharply raises its
Defense stat.

move_748.name: no-retreat
move_748.description:
This move raises all the user’s stats but prevents
the user from switching out or fleeing.

move_749.name: tar-shot
move_749.description:
The user pours sticky tar over the target, lowering the
target’s Speed stat. The target becomes weaker to
Fire-type moves.

move_750.name: magic-powder
move_750.description:
The user scatters a cloud of magic powder that
changes the target to Psychic type.

move_751.name: dragon-darts
move_751.description:
The user attacks twice using Dreepy. If there are two
targets, this move hits each target once.

move_752.name: teatime
move_752.description:
The user has teatime with all the Pokémon in the battle.
Each Pokémon eats its held Berry.

move_753.name: octolock
move_753.description:
The user locks the target in and prevents it from
fleeing. This move also lowers the target’s Defense
and Sp. Def every turn.

move_754.name: bolt-beak
move_754.description:
The user stabs the target with its electrified beak.
If the user attacks before the target, the power of this
move is doubled.

move_755.name: fishious-rend
move_755.description:
The user rends the target with its hard gills.
If the user attacks before the target, the power of this
move is doubled.

move_756.name: court-change
move_756.description:
With its mysterious power, the user swaps the effects on
either side of the field.

move_757.name: max-flare
move_757.description:
This is a Fire-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
The user intensifies the sun for five turns.

move_758.name: max-flutterby
move_758.description:
This is a Bug-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_759.name: max-lightning
move_759.description:
This is an Electric-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
The user turns the ground into Electric Terrain for
five turns.

move_760.name: max-strike
move_760.description:
This is a Normal-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This lowers the target’s Speed stat.

move_761.name: max-knuckle
move_761.description:
This is a Fighting-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This raises ally Pokémon’s Attack stats.

move_762.name: max-phantasm
move_762.description:
This is a Ghost-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This lowers the target’s Defense stat.

move_763.name: max-hailstorm
move_763.description:
This is an Ice-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
The user summons a hailstorm lasting five turns.

move_764.name: max-ooze
move_764.description:
This is a Poison-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This raises ally Pokémon’s Sp. Atk stats.

move_765.name: max-geyser
move_765.description:
This is a Water-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
The user summons a heavy rain that falls for
five turns.

move_766.name: max-airstream
move_766.description:
This is a Flying-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This raises ally Pokémon’s Speed stats.

move_767.name: max-starfall
move_767.description:
This is a Fairy-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
The user turns the ground into Misty Terrain for
five turns.

move_768.name: max-wyrmwind
move_768.description:
This is a Dragon-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This lowers the target’s Attack stat.

move_769.name: max-mindstorm
move_769.description:
This is a Psychic-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
The user turns the ground into Psychic Terrain for
five turns.

move_770.name: max-rockfall
move_770.description:
This is a Rock-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
The user summons a sandstorm lasting five turns.

move_771.name: max-quake
move_771.description:
This is a Ground-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This raises ally Pokémon’s Sp. Def stats.

move_772.name: max-darkness
move_772.description:
This is a Dark-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This lowers the target’s Sp. Def stat.

move_773.name: max-overgrowth
move_773.description:
This is a Grass-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
The user turns the ground into Grassy Terrain for
five turns.

move_774.name: max-steelspike
move_774.description:
This is a Steel-type attack Dynamax Pokémon use.
This raises ally Pokémon’s Defense stats.

move_775.name: clangorous-soul
move_775.description: The user raises all its stats by using some of its HP.

move_776.name: body-press
move_776.description:
The user attacks by slamming its body into the target.
The higher the user’s Defense, the more damage it can
inflict on the target.

move_777.name: decorate
move_777.description:
The user sharply raises the target’s Attack and Sp. Atk
stats by decorating the target.

move_778.name: drum-beating
move_778.description:
The user plays its drum, controlling the drum’s roots
to attack the target. This also lowers the target’s
Speed stat.

move_779.name: snap-trap
move_779.description:
The user snares the target in a snap trap for four to
five turns.

move_780.name: pyro-ball
move_780.description:
The user attacks by igniting a small stone and launching
it as a fiery ball at the target. This may also leave the
target with a burn.

move_781.name: behemoth-blade
move_781.description:
The user becomes a gigantic sword and cuts the target.
This move deals twice the damage if the target
is Dynamaxed.

move_782.name: behemoth-bash
move_782.description:
The user becomes a gigantic shield and slams into
the target. This move deals twice the damage if the
target is Dynamaxed.

move_783.name: aura-wheel
move_783.description:
Morpeko attacks and raises its Speed with the energy
stored in its cheeks. This move’s type changes
depending on the user’s form.

move_784.name: breaking-swipe
move_784.description:
The user swings its tough tail wildly and attacks
opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Attack stats.

move_785.name: branch-poke
move_785.description:
The user attacks the target by poking it with a sharply
pointed branch.

move_786.name: overdrive
move_786.description:
The user attacks opposing Pokémon by twanging
a guitar or bass guitar, causing a huge echo and
strong vibration.

move_787.name: apple-acid
move_787.description:
The user attacks the target with an acidic liquid created
from tart apples. This also lowers the target’s
Sp. Def stat.

move_788.name: grav-apple
move_788.description:
The user inflicts damage by dropping an apple from
high above. This also lowers the target’s Defense stat.

move_789.name: spirit-break
move_789.description:
The user attacks the target with so much force that it
could break the target’s spirit. This also lowers the
target’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_790.name: strange-steam
move_790.description:
The user attacks the target by emitting steam.
This may also confuse the target.

move_791.name: life-dew
move_791.description:
The user scatters mysterious water around and restores
the HP of itself and its ally Pokémon in the battle.

move_792.name: obstruct
move_792.description:
This move enables the user to protect itself from all attacks.
Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.
Direct contact harshly lowers the attacker’s Defense stat.

move_793.name: false-surrender
move_793.description:
The user pretends to bow its head, but then it stabs the
target with its disheveled hair. This attack never misses.

move_794.name: meteor-assault
move_794.description:
The user attacks wildly with its thick leek.
The user can’t move on the next turn, because the
force of this move makes it stagger.

move_795.name: eternabeam
move_795.description:
This is Eternatus’s most powerful attack in its original
form. The user can’t move on the next turn.

move_796.name: steel-beam
move_796.description:
The user fires a beam of steel that it collected from its
entire body. This also damages the user.

move_797.name: expanding-force
move_797.description:
The user attacks the target with its psychic power.
This move’s power goes up and damages all opposing
Pokémon on Psychic Terrain.

move_798.name: steel-roller
move_798.description:
The user attacks while destroying the terrain. This move
fails when the ground hasn’t turned into a terrain.

move_799.name: scale-shot
move_799.description:
The user attacks by shooting scales two to five times
in a row. This move boosts the user’s Speed stat but
lowers its Defense stat.

move_800.name: meteor-beam
move_800.description:
In this two-turn attack, the user gathers space power
and boosts its Sp. Atk stat, then attacks the target
on the next turn.

move_801.name: shell-side-arm
move_801.description:
This move inflicts physical or special damage,
whichever will be more effective. This may also poison
the target.

move_802.name: misty-explosion
move_802.description:
The user attacks everything around it and faints upon
using this move. This move’s power is increased on
Misty Terrain.

move_803.name: grassy-glide
move_803.description:
Gliding on the ground, the user attacks the target.
This move always goes first on Grassy Terrain.

move_804.name: rising-voltage
move_804.description:
The user attacks with electric voltage rising from
the ground. This move’s power doubles when the target
is on Electric Terrain.

move_805.name: terrain-pulse
move_805.description:
The user utilizes the power of the terrain to attack.
This move’s type and power changes depending on
the terrain when it’s used.

move_806.name: skitter-smack
move_806.description:
The user skitters behind the target to attack. This also
lowers the target’s Sp. Atk stat.

move_807.name: burning-jealousy
move_807.description:
The user attacks with energy from jealousy. This leaves
all opposing Pokémon that have had their stats boosted
during the turn with a burn.

move_808.name: lash-out
move_808.description:
The user lashes out to vent its frustration toward
the target. If the user’s stats were lowered during this
turn, the power of this move is doubled.

move_809.name: poltergeist
move_809.description:
The user attacks the target by controlling the target’s
item. The move fails if the target doesn’t have an item.

move_810.name: corrosive-gas
move_810.description:
The user surrounds everything around it with
highly acidic gas and melts away items they hold.

move_811.name: coaching
move_811.description:
The user properly coaches its ally Pokémon,
boosting their Attack and Defense stats.

move_812.name: flip-turn
move_812.description:
After making its attack, the user rushes back to
switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

move_813.name: triple-axel
move_813.description:
A consecutive three-kick attack that becomes more
powerful with each successful hit.

move_814.name: dual-wingbeat
move_814.description:
The user slams the target with its wings.
The target is hit twice in a row.

move_815.name: scorching-sands
move_815.description:
The user throws scorching sand at the target to attack.
This may also leave the target with a burn.

move_816.name: jungle-healing
move_816.description:
The user becomes one with the jungle, restoring HP
and healing any status conditions of itself and its ally
Pokémon in battle.

move_817.name: wicked-blow
move_817.description:
The user, having mastered the Dark style, strikes the
target with a fierce blow. This attack always results
in a critical hit.

move_818.name: surging-strikes
move_818.description:
The user, having mastered the Water style, strikes the
target with a flowing motion three times in a row. This
attack always results in a critical hit.

move_819.name: thunder-cage
move_819.description:
The user traps the target in a cage of sparking
electricity for four to five turns.

move_820.name: dragon-energy
move_820.description:
Converting its life-force into power, the user attacks
opposing Pokémon. The lower the user’s HP, the lower
the move’s power.

move_821.name: freezing-glare
move_821.description:
The user shoots its psychic power from its eyes
to attack. This may also leave the target frozen.

move_822.name: fiery-wrath
move_822.description:
The user transforms its wrath into a fire-like aura
to attack. This may also make opposing Pokémon flinch.

move_823.name: thunderous-kick
move_823.description:
The user overwhelms the target with lightning-like
movement before delivering a kick. This also lowers
the target’s Defense stat.

move_824.name: glacial-lance
move_824.description:
The user attacks by hurling a blizzard-cloaked
icicle lance at opposing Pokémon.

move_825.name: astral-barrage
move_825.description:
The user attacks by sending a frightful amount of small
ghosts at opposing Pokémon.

move_826.name: eerie-spell
move_826.description:
The user attacks with its tremendous psychic power.
This also removes 3 PP from the target’s last move.
